      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOONGALLA SHAZIA (3) had the drop on the lead from the rails draw last start but could only manage third, beaten 2.25 lengths (23.46) at this track in a Maiden over 390m. Good form should continue. HAVING A LOOK (1) is still a maiden after 45 runs but rarely out of the placings, the latest filling a minor again when fifth at Bendigo. Tends to run well here despite having never won. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings five times from eight attempts. Must be included in calculations. STILL THE SAME (5) turned in a plain effort last time when seventh at Wagga over 320m behind Boracay Player (19.14) in a Maiden. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Bold showing expected. HARTLAND MAISIE (8) is likely to have admirers.",
